Sign up here to get Andrew Marchand’s Sports Clicker delivered to your inbox each Monday morning. There is so much to analyze with all the big time NFL announcing moves, but let’s start with Fox’s decision to reward Joe Buck for nearly three decades of top-of-the-class work By allowing Buck to break out of the final year of his contract for a huge new deal that may reach five years, $75 million with ESPN’s “Monday Night Football,” Fox has decided to trust its process. Trusting the process: In letting Buck go, Fox Sports CEO Eric Shanks and executive producer Brad Zager are implementing a plan they have been cultivating for years to add depth and young talent to the network’s broadcasting roster.